                <h3>1. Incorrect HTTP Method Usage</h3>
                <p>RESTful APIs leverage HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH) to indicate the intended action on a resource. Misusing these methods leads to confusion, breaks caching mechanisms, and violates the principle of "safe" and "idempotent" operations.</p>
