            <ul class="problem-list">
                <li><strong>Incorrect HTTP Method:</strong> "POST" is used for creating resources or performing non-idempotent operations. Deleting a resource should use "DELETE".</li>
                <li><strong>Verb in URI:</strong> "delete" is a verb in the URI. URIs should identify the resource, not the action.</li>
                <li><strong>Inconsistent Naming:</strong> Uses "user" (singular) while other endpoints might use "users" (plural) for collections. Consistency is key.</li>
                <li><strong>Path Variable Placement:</strong> While <code>/5</code> is acceptable for an ID, the structure <code>/user/delete/{id}</code> is overly verbose and action-oriented.</li>
