                    <li><code>204 No Content</code>: If the resource was successfully deleted and no response body is returned (preferred for DELETE).</li>
                    <li><code>404 Not Found</code>: If a user with the specified ID does not exist.</li>
                    <li><code>401 Unauthorized</code>: If authentication is required but missing/invalid.</li>
                    <li><code>403 Forbidden</code>: If the authenticated user doesn't have permission to delete users.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <p><strong>Explanation:</strong> The DELETE method on the <code>/users/{id}</code> resource clearly indicates the intent to remove that specific user resource. The URI now consistently uses the plural "users" for the collection.</p>
